don't know why he didn't get webbed feet as much as 
he was drafted out. But there wasn't as much of

01:00.292 --> 01:01.755
that. Now there was a little of it over in the 
non-military. Somebody that you didn't like and

01:04.620 --> 01:09.169
you wanted to mess them up. Well, there's nothing 
much worse than a big bucket of water and a cot and a

01:09.189 --> 01:16.243
bed and a mattress because there ain't no going 
back to bed. The rest of the night you sit up and it's

01:17.145 --> 01:23.076
a lot of fun. and it's it's we got to where this old 
boy we drowned out we go in and wake him up and just

01:23.663 --> 01:48.642
he's set up we let him have it oh lord lord what kids 
won't do there's not in the book what was the food

01:23.663 --> 01:48.642
like in the mess hall i thought it was delightful i 
never did have a complaint about the food a lot of

01:23.663 --> 01:48.642
kids a lot of men boys complained about it. They 
said it wasn't any good, it was dirty, and the truth

01:51.078 --> 02:07.602
of the matter, the food was delicious, it was 
nutritious, and there wasn't a boy that ever went

01:51.078 --> 02:07.602
to A&M College that didn't grow fat and husky and 
healthy on the food. But as you could understand,

02:08.503 --> 02:17.216
preparing it in the quantities they did, 
certainly it didn't have the touch that Mama did at

02:08.503 --> 02:17.216
home. And naturally, there'd be some bitching 
about it, griping about it, but I never did feel

02:20.532 --> 02:26.282
that way about the food. In fact, I ate better at A&M 
than I had all my life because I ate well at home, but

02:26.342 --> 02:35.198
I worked like the devil, too. I mean, in the field, 
hard, and so I had no complaint about the food. I

02:40.748 --> 02:41.469
thought it was wonderful. Was there much variety, 
or did you have Oh, I thought we had a lot of variety.

02:46.215 --> 02:49.138
Now that there, I think, is part of the trouble. It 
was kind of a monotonous menu. In other words, on

02:51.820 --> 03:02.150
Monday you had this, Tuesday you had this, 
Wednesday you had this, Thursday and Friday you

02:51.820 --> 03:02.150
had this, and Saturday and Sunday. And you could 
almost sit down and write the menu for the whole

03:02.590 --> 03:07.554
week. And it did get monotonous in that sense. 
Well, it wasn't because it wasn't good or

03:12.254 --> 03:15.999
well-prepared or nutritious. You just kind of get 
tired of it. So if you could rake up a few extra

03:18.242 --> 03:27.975
dimes, you'd go over to Agland every now and then 
and have a meal that you ordered yourself, what you

03:18.242 --> 03:27.975
wanted, where you wanted. It wouldn't be a bit 
better food, but it's something you sat down and

03:27.995 --> 03:37.467
ordered and ate because you wanted it instead of 
having it set in front of you. Psychological

03:37.487 --> 03:41.012
dislike more than any actual dislike. Let's see, 
was

